arStrings.szText: "They say that it is incurable, everyone sick dies. That Aldara claimed to have a cure. That Brecht was the first to die."
Aye, it is deadly for all who became afflicted, though suddenly none have come down with the illness. It defies explanation!
As for Aldara, she was told to leave the town once we saw that her so-called cure was to touch the afflicted with an amulet. We do not allow the false hope of faith healers here.
Then the first death was not the first to come down with the illness, but the last? Strange. Brecht was a man from the north, though I will need to consult my records to recall more than that.
